### Hybrid Layer for Formatting

```python
class FormattingLayer:
    """
    Yjs handles text content via CRDT.
    Rich formatting (bold ranges, headings) uses
    OT-style transformations on top — this is what
    ProseMirror's y-prosemirror binding does internally.

    Key insight: Pure CRDT for structure,
    OT-inspired for attribute ranges.
    """

    def apply_format(self, range_start, range_end, attribute, value):
        # Represented as CRDT-compatible relative positions
        # so they survive concurrent insertions/deletions
        start_anchor = Y.createRelativePositionFromTypeIndex(
            self.ytext, range_start
        )
        end_anchor = Y.createRelativePositionFromTypeIndex(
            self.ytext, range_end
        )

        self.ytext.format(
            range_start, 
            range_end - range_start,
            {attribute: value}
        )
